WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.200
With Pandas, everything happens eagerly. You give the library some instructions, and it

00:00:05.200 --> 00:00:09.760
evaluates your instructions the moment you give them. Whereas Polars, it's got an option whereby

00:00:09.760 --> 00:00:14.800
you can give it some instructions, it can wait a bit, and then it can do them all together in

00:00:15.920 --> 00:00:20.799
the most optimal way that it can detect. If I was to tell you to cook me a recipe,

00:00:20.799 --> 00:00:25.840
and I gave you the steps one at a time, and you had to do the steps one at a time,

00:00:25.840 --> 00:00:29.360
and for each step go out and buy the ingredients that you need for that step,

00:00:29.360 --> 00:00:34.080
it's going to be a pretty inefficient way of making a cake. But if I can give you the recipe

00:00:34.080 --> 00:00:39.200
beforehand, and you can buy all the ingredients together, then maybe do two steps at the same time,

00:00:39.200 --> 00:00:41.840
you know, it's going to be a much nicer cooking experience.

